From 3a39d4c14896806ce5b406f19c45fb0848d436f9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sun Yuechi <sunyuechi@iscas.ac.cn>
Date: Mon, 29 Jun 2026 19:36:18 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] rgw: fix inverted MFA check in DeleteMultiObj for
 versioned objects

The MFA-delete guard in RGWDeleteMultiObj::execute() flagged a request
as targeting a versioned object when the version-id was empty, which is
exactly backwards: a non-empty version-id denotes a versioned delete and
is what S3 MFA-Delete must protect.

As written, a delete carrying a version-id bypassed the MFA check while a
plain delete spuriously required MFA. Test instance.empty() with the
correct sense so versioned deletes require MFA verification.

Signed-off-by: Sun Yuechi <sunyuechi@iscas.ac.cn>
---
 src/rgw/rgw_op.cc | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/rgw/rgw_op.cc b/src/rgw/rgw_op.cc
index bfcb0ea6df1..43c2fc30963 100644
--- a/src/rgw/rgw_op.cc
+++ b/src/rgw/rgw_op.cc
@@ -8358,7 +8358,7 @@ void RGWDeleteMultiObj::execute(optional_yield y)
     bool has_versioned = false;
     for (auto object : multi_delete->objects) {
       const string& instance = object.get_version_id();
-      if (instance.empty()) {
+      if (!instance.empty()) {
         has_versioned = true;
         break;
       }
